I jump at the sound of his voice but quickly recovered, "Hey, Aiden." His warm eyes and inviting smile told me he had been talking to Bee, not me. Blushing, I lowered my head. Boys preferred her to me, and I preferred it that way too. I had no interest in boys; hell, I didn\'92t want anything to do with pretty much anybody. Bee'd smile her coy smile that made boys think she liked \'91em. Not sure if she really did, but hoped, one day, she\'92d have the sense to kick every last one of them in the nuts, especially pa. \
