Folks around town hadn\'92t yet forgotten about Jacob. Most said to say hi, as if we talked to him every day. I wasn\'92t sure what to tell them about my brother. Not word from him since he left for the Army, but also no word from the Army either. That\'92s all I needed to believe he was safe. \
I watched Aiden as he helped Mrs. Carter with her bags; I envied his comfort around people, his ease at talking with them, his deftness at fitting in. Loyalty in his face, but betrayal in his actions. I knew. I\'92ve known him all my life, and over the decades as I vanished into the background, he stood out. Many wondered why he'd even come back here after graduating college. Potential, they said. If kids got out, they didn't come back. I wouldn\'92t.\
